# Playwright E2E Tests

ALL Playwright commands (test runs, installs, codegen) MUST use `required_permissions: ["all"]` on the Shell tool. Playwright launches real browser processes that require unrestricted sandbox access.

Before running tests, check if browsers are installed:

```bash
PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=0 npx playwright install --dry-run 2>&1 | head -5
```

If the output indicates browsers are missing, install only chromium:

```bash
npx playwright install chromium
```

To run tests:

```bash
cd frontend && npx playwright test e2e/<spec-file>.spec.ts --reporter=line
```

The Playwright config uses Vite dev server on port 4173 with `reuseExistingServer: true`.
